    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-02-15T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-02-15T20:00:00-05:00" n="61"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d61">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.79614/5: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Geissler</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-02-15T20:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 15, 1927—8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>13. Your despatch 1415, February 4.<note n="15" xml:id="d61fn15">Not printed; it
                        transmitted a copy of the proposed contract between Francisco Buch de Parada
                        and the Government of Guatemala.</note> Article 24 of the contract
                    apparently grants a virtual monopoly of air traffic between the points mentioned
                    in Article 1. Please call this to the attention of the appropriate authorities
                    and express the hope of this Government that no exclusive concession, preference
                    or monopoly will be granted which would deny to American citizens a fair and
                    equal opportunity to compete in commercial aviation in Guatemala.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
